The bat stocks in Scotland and the whole of the United Kingdom have fallen significantly in the last century.
They are threatened by construction and development work that affects sleeping places and leads to the loss of living space.
Windwheels and lighting can also pose a risk, as can fly-catchers and chemical treatment of building materials or attacks by domestic cats.
Bats are not really blind.
